tweet: Get to know the STD's that are in our community. According to the CDC, it is estimated that 1 in 20 sexually active young women aged 14-24 years has chlamydia. Visit  https://t.co/xzJmwCc7ie for more information.  https://t.co/ZGyjOETfFj

name: Stark County Health Department
tweet: STD's are on the rise in Stark County and services are provided to help. No one will be turned away for inability to pay for testing. Our health department is located at 7235 Whipple Ave. NW in North Canton's Park Centre Plaza. Call 330.493.9928 ext. 2047 for questions!  https://t.co/RiocESSb7X

name: Stark County Health Department
tweet: Our health department has been monitoring the STD situation in our county all year long. We have seen steady increases in both Chlamydia and Gonorrhea. It is important to be tested and to seek treatment. We can help! Call 330.493.9928 ext. 2047 for questions.  https://t.co/WWud442h2a
